SENATE BILL 1834
By Akbari
HOUSE BILL 1713
By Shaw
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 55,
Chapter 9, Part 4, relative to towing.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 55-9-414, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(h) Notwithstanding subsection (a), a recovery vehicle, as defined in § 55-8-132,
may display a single, steady-burning or flashing blue light to the rear, but not the front, of
the vehicle when stationary and engaged in the recovery of, or otherwise providing
assistance to, another vehicle.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
